                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4–2349: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-23">April 23,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received April 23—9:39 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>847. Posters now displayed throughout city stating Communists will take over
                    administration city 7 a. m. tomorrow. Mob looting continues. City power still
                    functioning. At least four ammunition dumps blown north and outside city.</p>
                <p>Sent Department; repeated Shanghai 433, Embassy Canton 293.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
